@*Behind the mask*@
<section id="calcuttaBehindTheMask" class="section">
    <div class="container">

        <h4>Behind the mask</h4>
        <P>
            <strong>
                Folk theatre originated probably in the first half of 16th Century with Mythology as the theme though there are evidences of storytelling through folk singing even earlier. Roughly round the end of 18th Century the first Bengali play was staged. But the proscenium theatre emerged during the British rule during the Bengal Renaissance. Bengali theatre which was already rich as an art form by then became a vehicle of mass education and an effort in reflecting the then society and politics. Many eminent personalities including the National Poet of India Rabindra Nath Tagore contributed majorly in Kolkata theatre through their work.
            </strong>
        </P>
        <p><strong>Bengali theatre has always dealt with magic realism and body language, so the use of performer's body along with the characterization is eminent and evolving. The language of theatre is also constantly changing.</strong></p>
        <p><strong>This tour takes you through the history of Bengali Theatre, visiting the heritage and contemporary theatres, costume and wig makers, printing press where theatre posters are printed, workshops where you get to meet and talk to the actors and watch them rehearse and ends with viewing a real theatre show.    </strong></p>
