            <strong>
                Jo Basu, a documentary film maker and teacher for under graduate film study students. Having done his graduation in History and Culture, finally found his passion in Media Studies and film making.  For last 12 years he is extensively researching and making documentaries. His films named Children of Soil, The Kiln, From the Shore, Wild Refugees, Death, Freedom, etc, deal on subjects like environmental pollution, children’s rights, women empowerment, tribal issues, wild life and many more.
            </strong>
        </P>
        <p>
            <strong>
                His films have gained acclimation in various International film festivals.<br />
                Salon Internacional de la Luz, Colombia<br />
                Inonu University 10th International Short Film Festival, Turkey<br />
                Rushes National Film Festival<br />
                Cinema Grand Prix, Bali, Indonesia…..and so on
            </strong>
        </p>
        <p><strong>You will get a chance to meet and spend a day with this talented director. You will get to know how he goes about making his films, the research he has to undertake and days of persuading his subjects because often it deals with sensitive issues like documenting a all women football team whose members all hail from conservative Muslim families. He will take you around the areas he has shot for his films and make you meet the subjects. You get all the inner information you always wanted to know about documentary film making in India. The day ends with a filming of one of his favourite ventures.     </strong></p>
